     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Using Gradepro\n",
    "\n",
    "## \"Render unto man the things which are man’s and unto the computer the things which are the computer’s\", Norbert Wiener, God and Golem (1964)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# This is how Gradepro looks like\n",
    "\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# The process of critical appraisal\n",
    "![From an article to Gradepro](conference.jpg)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Skills Needed\n",
    "\n",
    "## Analyse a Problem (\"Human\")\n",
    "## Use software tools to solve the problem (\"Computers\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Skills required to use a software tool is not taught in Epidemiology/health sciences courses"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Software Carpentry\n",
    "\n",
    "- Goal is to teach Competence in Computing\n",
    "- Started with the idea that scientists can do productive work if they learned how to compute\n",
    "- Short focused trainings are better than week long training\n",
    "- Peer helpers and live coding with frequent feedbacks while teaching helps to reinforce ideas\n",
    "([For a comprehensive article, see](http://bit.ly/2HhV8Uy) )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Software carpentry in action\n",
    "[Live coding](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vacuk_kNOz8)\n",
    "(Will bring up a youtube window)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# What was done\n",
    "- Students were provided a challenge to solve a critical appraisal topic\n",
    "- Students brought their own laptops to work \n",
    "- Instructor (the presenter) used his own laptop in the classroom\n",
    "- Students and the instructor worked together in a live coding session\n",
    "- Students were encourage to ask questions as they got stuck\n",
    "- The version of \"live coding\" was to work in the same room working on the same problem\n",
    "- Students worked in \"pairs\" that helped each other"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Lessons learned\n",
    "- It was modelled after software carpentry principles to merge critical appraisal with computing\n",
    "- Students needed hand holding \n",
    "- A web app for critical appraisal was useful\n",
    "- The grades of the students improved compared with demonstration alone \n",
    "- Verbal feedback from students suggested they liked this format\n",
    "- This strategy reduced the need for one on one sessions"
   ]
  },
